cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the security limitations of the CAN-Bus protocol and proposes solutions to overcome them.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the different layers of the in-vehicle network and how software solutions can improve the security of the system.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the communication between different Electronic Control Units (ECUs) in the vehicle and how it affects the overall system.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the different types of in-vehicle network protocols and bus systems.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the potential dangers of insecure in-vehicle networks and the impact on society.
